The intricate and winding landscape of the world’s tallest mountain has been captured from space.

Mount Everest’s snow-covered peaks are seen in stark contrast against the brown and barren landscape in this Nasa Earth Observatory satellite image.

It is one of 14 mountain peaks on Earth that stand taller than 26,000ft (8,000m) and the local Nepalese name for it is Sagarmatha, which means 'mother of the universe.'

