Despite its reputation as an extremely dangerous mountain, commercial guiding has done much to improve the safety of the Everest ascent.  

As of March 2012, there had been 5,656 successful ascents of Everest, although 223 people had died at fatality rate of 4 per cent.

The satellite image was taken in December, just weeks after Nasa captured the rivers of black lava snaking over the snow-covered slopes of the stratovolcano Mount Etna in Sicily.  

